    #!python
    from numpy import mgrid, pi, sin, ogrid
    from scipy.interpolate import interp2d
    y, x = mgrid[0:pi:20j, 0:pi:21j]
    z = sin(x+y)
    I = interp2d(x, y, z)



The leak:



    ==31126== 48 (40 direct, 8 indirect) bytes in 1 blocks are definitely lost in loss record 11 of 40
    ==31126==    at 0x40051F9: malloc (vg_replace_malloc.c:149)
    ==31126==    by 0x4434AF2: array_alloc (arrayobject.c:6437)
    ==31126==    by 0x443C59A: PyArray_NewFromDescr (arrayobject.c:5063)
    ==31126==    by 0x445268D: PyArray_FromArray (arrayobject.c:7580)
    ==31126==    by 0x4452765: PyArray_FromAny (arrayobject.c:8030)
    ==31126==    by 0x5E6DB56: fitpack_surfit (__fitpack.h:152)
    ==31126==    by 0x5F15D2C: PyCFunction_Call (in /usr/lib/libpython2.4.so.1.0)
    ...



The following happens at `__fitpack.h`, line 152:



    #!c
    ap_wrk=(PyArrayObject *)PyArray_ContiguousFromObject(wrk_py, PyArray_DOUBLE, 0, 1);



However, on a success return around line 227, only the following variables are DECREF'ed:



    #!c
    Py_DECREF(ap_x);
    Py_DECREF(ap_y); 
    Py_DECREF(ap_z);             
    Py_DECREF(ap_w);        



However, the error cleanup code does:



    #!c
