b"_Original ticket http://projects.scipy.org/scipy/ticket/225 on 2006-07-07 by @brickZA, assigned to @wnbell._

I remember succesfully using integer dtypes with sparse matrices before. Now it seems only floating point types are supported:

{{
In [1]: import numpy

In [2]: from scipy import sparse

In [3]: mat = sparse.lil_matrix((3,3), dtype=numpy.int8)

In [4]: mat.dtype
Out[4]: dtype('<f8')
}}}

In my code I have a very sparse matrix consisting only of values in [-1, 0, 1]. Using int8 saves quite a bit of memory. Of course I'm not solving the matrix, only using its matvec() method."
